Product: Clinora
Module: Authentication & Tenant Onboarding
Document Type: Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Version: 1.0
Status: Draft

1. Purpose

This document defines the functional and technical requirements for the Authentication and Tenant Management module of Clinora.

This module is the entry point to the platform and provides secure access for all users while ensuring complete tenant isolation between clinics.

The module supports onboarding new clinics, creating users, authenticating users, managing sessions, and enforcing role-based access control.

2. Business Objective

Provide a secure authentication system that allows multiple clinics to use the same Clinora platform while ensuring:

Secure login
Tenant isolation
Role-based access
User lifecycle management
Secure session management
Easy onboarding of new clinics
3. Actors
Actor	Description
Super Admin	Creates clinics and subscriptions
Clinic Admin	Manages clinic users
Reception	Uses assigned account
Doctor	Uses assigned account
Lab Staff	Uses assigned account
Patient	Registers and books appointments
4. User Stories
US-001

As a Super Admin,

I want to register a new clinic,

so that it can start using Clinora.

US-002

As a Clinic Admin,

I want to invite doctors,

so they can access the clinic.

US-003

As a Patient,

I want to create an account,

so that I can book appointments online.

US-004

As a User,

I want to login securely,

so I can access my dashboard.

US-005

As a User,

I want to reset my password,

so I can regain access if I forget it.

