16. Acceptance Criteria

A feature is complete when:

A Super Admin can create a clinic.
A Clinic Admin can invite users.
A Patient can register and log in.
Users receive JWT tokens after successful login.
Unauthorized users cannot access protected APIs.
Users can reset forgotten passwords.
Every request is restricted to the correct clinic.
All authentication events are recorded in audit logs.
17. Out of Scope (MVP)

The following features are planned for future releases:

Multi-factor authentication (MFA)
Single Sign-On (Google, Microsoft, Okta)
Social login
Biometric authentication
Passwordless login
Multiple active organizations per user
Fine-grained custom roles
Self-service clinic registration
18. Definition of Done

This module is considered complete when:

UI screens are implemented and approved.
Backend APIs match the OpenAPI specification.
Database migrations are applied successfully.
Unit and integration tests pass.
Authentication and authorization are validated.
Tenant isolation is verified.
Audit logging is operational.
CI/CD deployment succeeds.
QA signs off all acceptance criteria.
